The departure of the French troops from the base of Nijrab, which I observed from the top of the hills planted with almond trees thanks to French credits, was in order.
The convoys of trucks and armoured personnel joined Kabul without being attacked, flying over by helicopters.
There will be no Taliban outburst in Kabul by the end of 2014.
Circumstances have changed since their irresistible advance from 1994 to 1996.
