Pattloch referred to the lawsuits in which the court dismissed the complaint, as after a long period the criticized name had become a "market reality".
Pattloch explains to us that if the complainant is not lucky, he may even be forced to pay money to the plagiarist, because he would have harmed his brand in China.
In this area, the law of the jungle sometimes dominates.
