Some 400 carriers load the sulphur baskets on their shoulders from the bottom of the crater.
Despite its comfortable profits, the mining company has not mechanized the extraction of sulphur to save costs and does not provide any equipment to carriers who work on their own and are paid by weight.
In addition, they also do not receive a sub of the 30,000 rupees (2.50 euros) of increase per camera, in addition to the entry of 15,000 rupees (1.20 euros), which the guards of this natural park charge tourists who come to photograph the volcano and its human mules.
